<TITLE> Loby gets 13 years in jail for corruption </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)  A special court dealing with high-profile corruption cases Sunday sentenced former BNP lawmaker Ali Asghar Loby to 13 years in jail for amassing illegal wealth and suppressing information about his property. Judge of the special court-3 Shahed Nuruddin also sentenced Loby's wife Khushnud to three years in jail for aiding her husband to amass the illegal wealth. The court fined Loby Tk 1 million. Loby, a former president of the Bangladesh Cricket Board, will have to face another six months of imprisonment if he fails to pay the amount. bdne
